The paper deals with object classification in video streams, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The method used is a brain-inspired Hierarchical Temporal Memory (HTM) algorithm, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the system in terms of recognition accuracy, which is a common evaluation metric in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the authors mention the use of OpenCL for acceleration, which is a topic related to parallel computing and computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper deals with the classification of objects, which is a task related to natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.CL).
